  "prompt": "What do Israelis think of Jesus?",
  "response": "Views among Israelis about Jesus vary, as Israel is a diverse society with different religious and cultural perspectives:\n\n1. Jewish perspectives:\n- Many Jews view Jesus as a historical Jewish figure\n- Some see him as a rabbi or teacher\n- Generally do not accept him as the Messiah\n- Respect him as a Jewish historical figure, but do not believe he was divine\n\n2. Messianic Jews:\n- Believe Jesus is the Messiah\n- Blend Jewish cultural identity with Christian beliefs about Jesus\n\n3. Arab Israeli Christians:\n- Typically view Jesus as the Son of God and Messiah\n- Fully embrace Christian theological understanding of Jesus\n\n4. Secular Israelis:\n- Often view Jesus primarily as a historical/cultural figure\n- May have limited religious interest or strong opinions about him\n\n5. Orthodox Jews:\n- Generally view references to Jesus neutrally or negatively\n- Do not accept Christian theological claims about him\n\nOverall, perspectives are complex and individualized, reflecting Israel's religious and cultural diversity. Most Jews respect Jesus as a historical figure but do not share Christian theological interpretations of his role and identity.",
